// returns char*** plus parallel returnColumnSizes and returnSize arrays AND
// the caller has to own every substring. A faithful implementation needs
// dynamic growth of the outer result array, the inner column-sizes array,
// and a strdup per palindromic substring — pages of malloc bookkeeping that
// obscure the algorithmic idea (try every palindromic prefix, recurse).
// The other five languages cover the canonical backtracking solution; the
